author: eTN Managing Editor
title: Turkish Airlines will operate Baghdad flight from a different airport
text:
Turkish Airlines will operate Baghdad flight from a different airport 
Turkish Airlines inaugurates Baghdad (Iraq) flights to be operated from/to Istanbul Sabiha Gökçen International Airport. 
Already having the world's 4th largest flight network and flying to 278 destinations in 110 countries, Turkish Airlines continues to grow by adding a new flight destination operated from/to Istanbul Sabiha Gökçen International Airport. 
Beginning October 25th, roundtrip flights between Istanbul and Baghdad will be operated 2 times per week in both directions till November 23rd, and will be daily as from that. Oct 25, 2015
